Drug Control
Components of tr,\e United States' programmatic international drug control program include eradication, interdiction, and investigation and prosecution. Crop eradication eliminates drug supplies and increases the costs of drug trafficking. Effective interdiction reduces the flow of drugs and curbs the diversion of precursor chemicals necessary for drug production. Investigators and prosecutors, through the exchange of information with members of the international community (using mechanisms such as mutual legal assistance treaties), immobilize drug trafficking organizations by incarcerating their members, seizing their drugs, and

